caption: Take the time to get to know the staff, they will tell you about the history of the building and restaurant.  The food is amazing we had the pasta jambalaya and the tomato mozzarella salad.

Really great place for a quiet(ish) dinner in the French Quarter. I recommend sitting on the balcony outside to get the full experience, but the inside is really cool too. If I can make only one recommendation to you it is this: TRY THE GUMBO. It is absolutely amazing. Their other food is great, don't get me wrong, but the gumbo is the absolute best thing they offer and it is truly special.
I love the ambience but the menu is limited and the food was just ok and overpriced. Service was slow.

Stumbled into this place (literally) for a desert that was mind blowing! They were so hospitable that we decided to have our last dinner in town there. It did not disappoint, and quickly became one of our favorite places. We will be back!
The music was great, the food was seasoned very well. I will not speak on the management or the bartender.

We ate here for our anniversary dinner. They really take care of you. Our waiter Thomas was so helpful and also very entertaining. He was able to suggest items on the menu that would suit our taste. Food was VERY good. We had the blacken redfish and trout. Crabcakes were AMAZING! They don't skimp on crab and the sauce was spot on.  Gavin made sure our water glasses never became close to empty. Highly recommend.
Great atmosphere and the sazerac was above average. I had the gulf fish toujours and was pleased. The portions to price could use some work to get a 5th star. The live music was bonus.

Simply put, southern hospitality at its finest. Our server, Thomas, was incredible. Personable and knowledgeable about the wonderful menu. We had the gumbo and turtle soup and both were amazing! For entrees, we had the sirloin and stuffed red fish,  and they did not disappoint! Our drinks were tasty and the dessert crepes were delicious. This made our Valentine's day celebration very special!
A trip to NOLA is incomplete without dinner here.  Great food, superb wait staff, entertainment and atmosphere. A must.

My experience here was absolutely fantastic, the staff was incredibly nice, the music was nice, and the food was absolutely amazing.  The gumbo was my favorite.  My only complaint is that the lighting was a bit too dark.  Everything else was perfect though.

The food was AWESOME! Oyster appetizer, Filet and Pork-chop! Pork Chop  was the best, melted  in your mouth.....  Staff nailed it.  Kevin, Anjelique, a Brandon sre rock stars!  The best compliment tthat I have is you will not find a better  dinner experince ii. NOLA.

All I have to say is WOW are we impressed!! The seafood gumbo was *heavy* on the seafood, not watered (or chickened) down like a lot of places.  We got the blackened fish du jour, it was redfish last night, and it was seasoned and cooked to perfection.  I've eaten a lot of redfish in this city and I can confidently say this was my favorite so far.  It came with asparagus and the most delicious creamy sauce.  Even their starter garlic bread was decadent and just crunchy enough.
Every thing was great from the food too the drinks and even the servers
beautiful interior and bar. Thomas took excellent care of us, we enjoyed every dish especially the trout and fried oysters. Staff made us feel at home. Great experience!

This place is great. Went for a 30th birthday party with 8 people. They even let me order a decorated plate of cake ahead of time for the birthday girl. It wasn't very crowded on Friday at 8pm which was surprising considering the food was incredible. The filet and pork chop were our favorites. The sauce with both was so good. Location is perfect walking distance to Bourbon or Frenchman st to go out after dinner. It is white table cloth and we spent about 50$ a person including 2 bottles of wine for 8 people. Oh and the chocolate cake was incredible and definitely shareable.
We went here for my boyfriend's birthday. It was one of the best meals I've ever had. The service was phenomenal. Try the turtle soup!

Definitely among the best food I've had in my life. I've been here twice for dinner now, and Sbisa is going to be a guaranteed stop anytime I'm back in NOLA.  The bar and music are awesome; this would be a great place to even stop in and grab a drink, but you'd be doing yourself a disservice to not eat too. The food menu is short but sweet. The turtle soup, crab cakes, & oysters are great. The BBQ Shrimp is fantastic, and makes a very good shared appetizer for the table. I've also ordered the Trout Eugene and Court bouillon, which were both phenomenal.

What a pleasure. It's become our "go to" Jazz Brunch for every trip to New Orleans. Established in 1899 - so lots of character. Jazz band was wonderful! Service is so 1st class. With a party of 7, when our food came they gathered enough servers to deliver all our plates at exactly the same time. Bottomless Mimosas were immediately refilled if they were 1/2 empty. Today's special Country gumbo was overloaded with seafood... Turtle soup was also very good. 2 different Omelettes ordered, both wonderful, as was the shrimp and grits and eggs Benedict. Too full for desert, so instead had a yummy chocolate martini made with pecan vodka! Birthday boy got a complementary bread pudding with ice cream topped with run caramel and chocolate It's our favorite and happy to share with our friends!

I could not recommend this place highly enough.

As we walked into Cafe Sbisa we were greeted with a warm and friendly smile, and seated promptly. The restaurant is absolutely beautiful, romantic and full of New Orleans charm. It was the best meal and dining experience on our trip. The staff is very attentive, friendly and extremely professional. Our waitress Jakia was fantastic! Thank you! Sean has been there since 1899 😉 his hospitality and history of the restaurant is outstanding. First course, Crab cakes absolutely delicious and one of the best we have ever had! Second course, hubby had the chicken and sausage gumbo was very yummy and I enjoyed the corn and crab bisque...Omgoodness! Third course, we ordered the Blackened Red fish and the Trout Eugene both were fantastic and perfectly prepared. For Dessert we ordered the Banana pudding parfait creamy and delicious with layers of banana cake and candy pecans that added a delicious crunch. Thank you for a wonderful evening we will definitely be back for another delicious dinner.

Extremely disappointing and offensive! We were the first arrivals for brunch this morning and we had reservations.  We were seated on the balcony at a table for 2 in the sun.  There were 4 other tables on the balcony, 3 of them in the shade of umbrellas and one other one like ours for 2, in the sun.  We asked if we could be seated at one of the tables in the shade and were told no because those were reserved for 4 tops.  Another couple arrived and they were seated at the other table in the sun and they also asked the hostess if they could be seated at a table in the shade.  This time, the answer was, “well, we usually reserve those for 4 people seatings but I can go check and see if we can move you there.”  I said, “wait a minute, we already tried that also and you said no”.  The couple remained at their assigned table, but just like us, became very hot, quickly.  I asked if we could be moved to a table indoors and the hostess said she would check.  After a while, she came back and said that all other tables were reserved and there was no other place to seat us.  The only other party that was ever seated on the balcony while we were there, was a party of 3.  During the meal, I moved my chair a couple of feet away from our table, into the shade of one of the umbrellas because I was starting to burn.  The manager (named Scott) came over and said to me, “Ma’am you are going to have to move your chair back to your table”.  I said, “Oh is someone arriving for the table next to us now?”  He said, “Yes”.  So, I moved my chair forward again to our table, back in the sun.  No one ever came for that table.  Ten minutes went by.  It was offensive and so unkind of him to do that to me.  Totally unnecessary and downright mean.  We finished our starter and our cocktails and decided to leave.  We spent 30 minutes in the full, hot sun for no reason whatsoever.  The water tasted like dish soap.  The food that we did have was mediocre.  The manager, Scott, was a jerk.  Enough said.

Went to NOLA with the homies for my bachelor's party. We wanted one night that was a proper sit down restaurant to enjoy a great meal, drink some wine, and just boss up. Did some research before heading down to NOLA and with the great reviews and hearing there was a live band, decided to book a reservation at Sbisa. As soon as you step in, you feel the atmosphere here. The staff were very attentive, professional, and on point. Absolutely no hiccups with their service. The food.... It was excellent! Ordered the catch of the day and added the BBQ shrimp to the place. The shrimp was probably the most flavourful shrimp I have ever had in my life, no joke! The fish was cooked very well too but the shrimp was certainly a game changer. We enjoyed each other's company, paired with great wine, live music, and food. The dinner really set us up right for a night out in the Big Easy. Thank you, Cafe Sbisa staff!

We dined at Sbisa on our last night in NOLA.  We wanted an authentic NOLA dining experience without all the hubbub and pomp.  We considered the mainstay restaurants like Brenans or Arnaud's but settled in Sbisa.  Located near the French Market it is far from the bustle of Bourbon St.    It does not look like much from the outside but was elegant and comfy inside. Service was wonderful from the moment we entered.  Only glitch was our server did not bring bread which the Maitre d' caught and corrected.  The food was excellent.   We enjoyed each dish for our 3 course meal. Price was reasonable for the quality and taste of the food although not cheap.  We were also entertained by three wonderful musicians who played a mix of RnB and classic Jazz.  We met them outside and they were total gentlemen.    Overall Sbisa is a great dining option if you don't mind getting off Bourbon St.

I made a reservation for our brunch group for brunch on today, June 24th. The establishment was amenable when it came to the reservation and accommodating with our seating for service. When we arrived, we were seated and everything was awaiting us. Our party was the largest there and the restaurant wasn’t busy even while we enjoyed our meal. One of our members ordered the steak and eggs medium rare. She repeated the order to the server twice which repeated it back to her. However when her order was brought out, it came out medium well and she was able to tell when she cut into it. She sent the item back so her steak could be cooked properly. She was approached by the manager at the time, Scott Stage who pulled her to the side and stated that she could not receive another steak and then proceeded to tell her that she told the server the incorrect order and she, the customer was responsible for the cost of the steak. The member alerted me of the situation and I went to speak to Mr. Stage who’s demeanor gave off the impression of poor customer service and management. He stated that they are not a “corporate” restaurant like others and orders cannot be replaced. I then stated that one other member had ordered crab cakes that were too salty and they were replaced promptly, how was that situation any different? I explained to him that clearly a mistake was made and a customer shouldn’t have to pay for a meal they didn’t get to eat. He also stated that the Executive Chef Who is the owner would be telling me the same thing if he were here. That she would Have to pay for the meal regardless whether it was correct or not. He then had the server give her account of the situation with the member there and when I addressed him and told him that she will not pay for a meal she didn’t enjoy, he said he didn’t want to “argue about that and to go ahead and give her another steak and get them the check so they can get out of here.” He then walked away. His attitude was deplorable and so is his work ethic. I nor the 20 other ladies that are apart of our brunch group will patron there ever again. I’ve been to finer establishments than this and have been to everyday establishments and have never been treated as I was today. Our 1100 bill was paid in full (including the steak my member never received) which includes the 20% gratuity. You would think you’d get better service for that kind of patronage.

Delicious food and Excellent staff
Great food, beautiful building. Friendly staff 😊
Absurdly delicious creative spins on Creole faire. A must visit.
The food there is absolutely fabulous I enjoy going there and everyone who comes there I think they enjoy it as well
The good restaurant in the right place
Excellent Happy Hour, historic, and outstanding bartender.  Au gratin was legit.

Great Food and Great Customer Service! They even took the time to charge our phones. The staff stated "this is your home". They offered great advice on places to see. My New Orleans trip was complete because of this place!

Fell in love as soon as I walking in the door !! The atmosphere was excellent the appetizers where like a piece of heaven! So excited I haven't even got to the many course yet and had to write a review . the staff was extremely friend !! I will definitely make. A point to come here every time I come to new orlean
Great food and service. Very old fashioned style. Great mural over the bar.
Very nice. Third oldest restaurant in NOLA. I had a salad and crab cakes. I liked it and the service was great! Not a lot of meal choices though. I highly recommend.
Very original place, with live music and delicious food.

An explosion of beautiful flavors equally balanced with the right amount of kick. This stablishment is top notch! The attention to detail is beyond the average human understanding ! 10 stars .... open a restaurant like this in D.C.
Ok food nice staff

Amazing gumbo. Amazing food. Seriously the best food I have ever had in this city. Staff was so very friendly and seemed to love their jobs there. Prices were very reasonable for the amazing quality of the meal.This will be my new go to place to eat in New Orleans.
Must try trout Eugene and crab cakes.

Really good meal, very warm welcome, especially since we had never been. Met people who go several times in a week, every time they come to NO. Charmaine Neville does the lounge singer thing on Friday night's which is a perfect accompaniment to dinner!
This palace has amazing food. My first time in New Orleans and had dinner for my girlfriend's birthday. We were more than satisfied.
Delicious food!
Great food and good staff
Wonderful food , great service and live music through out lunch. So glad we stumbled upon this great restaurant!

We were a 4 top table for dinner on a busy Saturday night, the service was on point. The wait staff were very knowledgeable on the menu items as well as the bar selections. Our table chose to share 3 different appetizers and 4 different entrees to share. The Chef, Alfred Singleton, was on fire with his creations tonight. We could not choose a favorite tonight. Thanks Chef for a great dining experience.
I had a fine meal and the service was fine.

Beautiful New Orleans restaurant.  Wonderful ambiance.  The old architecture is beautiful and inviting. Excellent service. Friendly and courteous staff. Chef Albert even gave us the Grand Tour and a history lesson of the building. An exceptional meal. The oyster appetizer is to die for. The redfish dish was excellent as well as the seafood gumbo. Well worth the visit!

Service was flat out amazing. Our waiter, Giovanni, was absolutely wonderful. The food was incredible. I've eaten in many places around New Orleans, and this is definitely one of the best experiences I've had. From the live music, to the historic building, you'll find someone to love at this fantastic Decatur Restaurant.
Very good Cajun food. Great live music, not so loud you can't talk. Great atmosphere.
Ambience, great food, friendly staff...Good music. It all fits together.
Great food!!! Amazing brunch. BBQ shrimp was top notch.
Great spot for dinner

Had the gumbo. Presentation was nice and fancy. Also had red wine. The service was impeccable, the food was great. The atmosphere is slightly fancy but also comfortable. Right across from fremch market. There was live music and singing. It was awesome

Arrived in NO on a very delayed flight and was looking for a quiet, nice dining experience...away from the Bourbon St. area I was staying in. The restaurant suggested to me couldn't seat me (busy Friday night) and I popped my head into Sbisa's , down the street, and went in. What a find!  Great service staff and the food was spectacular. Loved it so much, that when friends (on a reunion) came in the next day, we couldn't score a reservation at several of the places they suggested, I took them back to Sbisa's.....and they're still raving about it.

Best Crab cakes I have ever had.  My son had the French toast (I don't remember the actual name of the dish) and said "this is better than ihop" in front of Alfred the chef.  I'm still laughing at that.  Fine Dining. A rare occasion that I ate slow so it wouldn't end.  I shouldn't feel this way about food.
Loved the atmosphere, the food and the music during brunch. Excited to come again during dinner!
Cool little spot in the French Quarter
Food was really good. A bit warm in this really old building. Portions could be bigger! Live blues music band plays during dinner.
Fantastic service, terrific music and atmosphere.  The best frog legs I have ever eaten.  I'be never written a review.....but just had to here.
Great drinks and service, didn't get to taste the food but heard other people raving about it :) The place has alot of history and both times we've been the staff is very knowledgeable of it.

Chicken was not undercooked, it was raw. A couple of bites into my chicken and waffles, I realized the chicken was completely raw. I sent it back. The server tried to take the easy way out by offering a free drink. I refused. He then offered to comp my dish(not meal). At this point it is common practice for the manager to come and apologize. The manager avoided me like the plague. They clearly don't understand the severity of serving raw chicken. It's not steak or fish. A few more bites and I would have become ill. My party and I should have got up and walked out. And you should avoid walking in.
Great music and love the food! Wonderful place to have a seat and enjoy the best of New Orleans!
Try the one eyed burger it was clutch two thumbs up

Excellent drinks and customer service. I looked all over town for an original Strawberry Daiquiri. It wasn't on the drink menu, and Mackenzie (the bartender) didn't have the strawberry liqueur the recipe calls for, but she improvised and made one especially for me.
Friendly atmosphere, great drink specials,  amazing cajun mac & cheese.  Megan and Joseph are great managers.  I loved laughing and hearing about the art on the walls.  Great history here.
Great music; nice low key service. Decent food albeit limited menu. Worthy leisurely evening.
Food was good, drinks tasty, wait staff very friendly and helpful. Really enjoyed the live music too. Multiple floors, so lots of room.
Another place with great music, just happened to dance our way into it.

We visited the bar twice. Not for the food, but because of the amazing music. There was a band fronted by a soulful women that drew us in. They play an early evening set on Friday and Saturday. Well worth checking out. We were so impressed with the music that we returned to see them play the next day.  Well worth checking out!

The food was amazing.  My husband got the seafood gumbo and cajun mac and cheese.  I had the oyster po boy.  We were both beyond pleased with the service and loved the food.  Would go there again.  Price was very reasonable for the quality of the food
